title: On Tokyo's heartbreak, Manu Bhaker says 'let the past remain in the past'
description: Indian shooter Manu Bhaker made history by winning two medals at the same Olympics post-Independence. Bhaker, alongside Sarabjot Singh, secured a bronze in the 10m air pistol mixed team event in Paris. This follows her earlier bronze win in the women's 10m air pistol event. Bhaker's achievement showcases her resilience after a disappointing Tokyo Olympics.

title: Kumari Selja ‘CM face’ in Haryana Congress posters, rift with Hooda faction widens
description: The rift between Haryana Congress factions led by Bhupinder Singh Hooda and the SRB group has intensified post-Lok Sabha elections. Despite encouraging results, differing factions are projecting rival leaders for the chief ministerial post. Selja's group released a poster excluding Hooda, signaling internal discord. The state party leadership has yet to comment officially on the matter.

title: Who is Sarabjot Singh, India's latest Olympic medallist
description: Sarabjot Singh, who transitioned from aspiring footballer to accomplished shooter, secured India's second medal at the Paris Olympics alongside Manu Bhaker by winning bronze in the 10m Air Pistol Mixed Team event. Despite initial financial concerns, his family supported his shooting ambitions, leading to significant national and international accolades, all under the mentorship of coach Abhishek Rana.

title: Techie loses Rs 28L to dating scam; police reveals how he was trapped
description: An engineering graduate in Visakhapatnam lost over Rs 28 lakh in an online dating scam. Fraudsters from Telangana created fake profiles to build a romantic relationship with the victim and then manipulated him into transferring money. They also blackmailed him with personal information. Police identified one suspect and are searching for others.

title: Paris Olympics Day 4 (July 30): India's Full Schedule & Results
description: Indian shooter Manu Bhaker secured her second Olympic medal alongside Sarabjot Singh by winning the bronze in the 10m air pistol mixed team event. The Indian men’s hockey team will face Ireland, and various Indian athletes, including archers and boxers, will be competing in their respective events. Key events for Day 4 have been scheduled.

title: Bhaker first Indian to win two medals at same Olympics post-Independence
description: Manu Bhaker became the first Indian to win two medals in a single Olympics post-Independence. She won a bronze in the 10m air pistol individual event and another bronze in the mixed team event. Bhaker and Sarabjot Singh won the bronze-medal match in Paris, securing India's second medal in the Summer Games. This achievement is a significant milestone in Indian sports history.

title: For SC-STs, funding IIT studies is tougher than cracking JEE
description: On August 1, IIT-Tirupati welcomed new students including Bonila Aryan Roshan from Telangana's Siddipet district. Despite securing admission in chemical engineering with a JEE rank of 2406 (SC category), Roshan faces financial uncertainties. Like several marginalized students, he struggles to cover costs beyond tuition fees, highlighting a significant issue in higher education access for underprivileged communities.

title: Bill Gates’ son-in-law to compete in Paris Olympics 2024
description: Nayel Nassar, husband of Bill Gates' daughter Jennifer Gates, is set to represent Egypt in the equestrian jumping event at the Paris Olympics. Nassar previously competed in the 2020 Tokyo Olympics. He aims for his first Olympic medal amid controversy about his support team size. Jennifer Gates prepares for their second child. Melinda Gates publicly supported Nassar on social media.

title: At 36°C, ‘cold desert’ Leh too hot for flights; 12 cancelled in 3 days
'India is incredibly delighted': PM Modi lauds Manu & Sarabjot
description: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi congratulated Indian shooters Manu Bhaker and Sarabjot Singh for winning the bronze medal in the 10m mixed team event at the Paris Olympics. Modi expressed pride and delight in their success, highlighting their skills and dedication. Bhaker was praised for her second consecutive Olympic medal, highlighting India's delight in their achievement.

title: CoinDCX co-founder slams rival crypto exchange WazirX's '55/45 plan'
description: WazirX, after suffering a massive $230 million security breach, proposed a controversial 55/45 loss distribution plan among users. CoinDCX's Sumit Gupta criticized this approach, urging WazirX to take financial responsibility from its reserves instead. Users reacted with significant backlash, concerned about the fairness and potential impacts on the broader crypto ecosystem.

title: 'Nightmares every week, is this governance?' Oppn on rail accidents
description: Opposition parties, including Congress and Trinamool Congress, criticized the BJP-led government following the Howrah-Mumbai Mail derailment in Jharkhand, which resulted in two deaths and 20 injuries. The opposition parties accused the Railway Ministry of lacking accountability. Previous incidents were also highlighted, questioning the effectiveness of the 'Kavach' safety system and overall governance.

title: 'Don't be a bi**h': Startup founder shares horrors of hiring
Paris Games: Manu Bhaker wins second Olympic medal
description: Manu Bhaker and Sarabjot Singh secured a bronze medal in the 10m air pistol team event in Paris, defeating Korea with a score of 16 to 10. The Indian duo had tallied 580 points, narrowly missing the gold medal match by one point. Meanwhile, another Indian team, Rhythm Sangwan and Arjun Singh Cheema, finished in 10th place.

title: To 'curb love jihad', UP proposes life imprisonment for accused
description: The Uttar Pradesh assembly considered a bill to amend the Unlawful Conversion of Religion Act, raising the maximum punishment to life imprisonment and a Rs 5 lakh fine. The amendment, introduced by Parliamentary Affairs Minister Suresh Khanna, targets forced conversions through threats, marriage, or trafficking, allowing any person to report such crimes.

title: A319 'Faridabad' flight gets stranded on busy Kolkata stretch
description: In Kolkata, a 110-foot retired Airbus A319 on a tractor trailer caused traffic disruption near Dakshineswar. The aircraft, destined to be a restaurant in Faridabad, got stuck while reversing at Vivekananda Setu, attracting many curious onlookers. This was the last of five planes bought by Moni Ji Enterprises for creative repurposing.

title: Delhi IAS coaching centre deaths: SUV driver asks 'why I am being blamed?'
description: Manoj Kathuria, accused of causing a flood leading to the deaths of three students in Old Rajender Nagar, denied any intent or knowledge of their presence. He claimed his vehicle's speed was manageable. The Delhi court sent him and four others to judicial custody till August 12, pending their bail plea hearing.

title: Babus skipping Independence-Day event may face action
description: Cabinet secretary Rajiv Gauba instructed all secretaries to ensure invited officials attend the Independence Day celebration at Red Fort. Gauba emphasized that absences would be taken seriously and reminded officers of their duty to participate in this national event. The advisory was issued to ensure better compliance this year, as many had previously failed to attend.

title: Budget 2024 three times UPA's last Budget in 2014: PM Modi at CII
description: PM Modi on Budget 2024: PM Modi said that India, which is currently the world’s fifth largest economy, will soon become the third largest. He also noted the time when India had been ranked among the ‘Fragile Five’ economies in the world.

title: Watch: Passenger goes berserk after served non-veg by 'mistake'
description: A video of an altercation between a passenger and pantry staff has gone viral on social media after the passenger, who was a vegetarian was mistakenly served non-vegetarian food. The event snowballed into chaos after the agitated passenger "gave two tight slaps" to the waiter upon finding out it was non-veg that he had consumed.

title: Pakistan beggar found unconscious with over PKR 5 lakh, Saudi passport in pocket
description: An elderly beggar was discovered unconscious on Khushab Road in Pakistan's Sargodha district with over Rs 0.5 million in his pocket by the Rescue 1122 team. He had PKR 534,000 and a passport showing multiple trips to Saudi Arabia. ​​Upon discharge from the hospital, he retrieved his money and belongings, according to Geo News.

title: August 2024 Bank Holidays: Banks closed up to 13 days
description: August 2024 Bank Holidays: In August, banks across India were closed for up to 13 days due to Sundays, national holidays, and regional festivals. Key closures included Ker Puja in Agartala, Tendong Lho Rum Faat in Sikkim, Patriot's Day in Manipur, and Independence Day nationwide.

title: In PM Modi's 'Amritkaal' empty pockets of citizens also being extracted: Rahul
description: Rahul Gandhi criticized the Centre for collecting substantial penalties from public sector bank customers who failed to maintain the required average monthly balance, calling it part of a scheme by PM Modi to burden the average Indian. His comments followed a Lok Sabha reply revealing that banks collected Rs 8,500 crore in penalties over five years. He likened the situation to an inescapable trap for common citizens.

title: Twin meteor showers to peak within 24 hrs; when & where to watch
'I don't dream like Mungerilal': Brij Bhushan on BJP ticket again
description: Former BJP MP and Wrestling Federation of India chief Brij Bhushan Sharan Singh, facing sexual harassment charges, did not expect another ticket from his party. While visiting Gonda district, he acknowledged this likelihood. He was removed from his position last year following protests by wrestlers. The trial against him began last week, and he pleaded not guilty.

title: More trouble for IAS officer Puja Khedkar as dept of personnel seeks response on allegations
description: ‘Action will be considered if she doesn’t respond’

title: 'Need job to earn money': Manu Bhaker's coach Jaspal Rana reveals
description: Olympic medalist Manu Bhaker's coach, Jaspal Rana, has been struggling financially since the Tokyo Olympics due to lack of a steady job and income. Despite guiding Bhaker to her historic bronze in Paris, Rana has not received salary support from the National Rifle Association of India for three years, compelling him to seek employment urgently.

title: Will income tax return filing deadline be extended?
description: ITR Filing FY 2023-24 deadline extension: Despite numerous technical issues on the e-filing portal, such as problems with Aadhaar-based OTP authentication, slow page loading, and upload errors, it is improbable that the deadline will be extended unless there is a significant technical issue on the website.

title: Morning bonhomie and a day of mixed signals in UP BJP
Watch: Local man refuses to return match ball during TNPL game
description: In a Tamil Nadu Premier League 2024 match, a Siechem Madurai Panthers pacer's delivery was struck over the fence by a Chepauk Super Gillies batsman. The ball was caught by a local man who refused to return it, expressing his frustration and walking away with it. The Panthers won the match by 9 runs.

title: '10 years of the UPA were ... ': Piyush Goyal hits back at Rahul on Budget speech
Melania thought ‘worst had happened' as she watched shooting live on TV: Trump
description: The former US President Donald Trump, who narrowly survived a shot at his life during a Pennsylvania rally, revealed on Monday that the former first lady Melania Trump was watching it live and was left traumatized so much so that she still struggles to talk about the day he dropped to the ground. And at that moment, Donald Trump said Melania had "thought the worst had happened.”

title: Howrah-Mumbai Mail derailed in Jharkhand, two dead, 18 injured
description: A medical team of the Chakrdharpur division of South Eastern Railways (SER) has reached the site of the accident. “The injured have been brought to the Chakradharpur railway hospital and are being treated,” railway officials said.

title: Arvind Kejriwal had direct role in excise ‘scam’: CBI chargesheet
description: CBI submitted a 200-page chargesheet against Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal and others after investigating alleged irregularities in the Delhi Excise Policy 2021-22. Kejriwal is accused of playing a direct role in manipulating the policy to benefit a liquor cartel. The chargesheet includes new evidence and mentions significant financial contributions to AAP by involved parties.

title: Navi Mumbai woman murder: Dawood arrested
description: The crime branch arrested Dawood Shaikh, aged 24, from his hometown in Gulbarga for the murder of 20-year-old Yashashri Shinde. Shaikh allegedly killed Shinde after she rejected his love proposal. The victim was found with severe injuries. Her family had previously filed a molestation complaint against Shaikh in 2019.

title: Shoaib Ibrahim's father reacts to rumours of him participating in BB18
description: The countdown to Bigg Boss 18 has begun, with Salman Khan confirmed as the host. Despite speculation, Shoaib Ibrahim will not participate in this season. Shoaib’s father believed Shoaib’s straightforward nature made him unsuitable for the show. Shoaib clarified the rumors, stating he might join in a few years and nearly lost a project due to the confusion.

title: Virat Kohli delights fans with memorable photo moments
description: India have secured victory in the three-match T20I series against Sri Lanka, establishing an insurmountable 2-0 advantage.The ODI series is set to commence on August 2 in Colombo, with all three matches scheduled to take place at the R Premadasa International Cricket Stadium. The second ODI will be held on August 4, and the series will reach its conclusion on August 7.

title: Olympics: Men's triathlon postponed due to pollution in Seine
description: The men's triathlon at the Paris Olympics was postponed due to high pollution levels in the Seine. Organizers rescheduled the event for Wednesday after heavy rains dirtied the river. If bacteria levels remain too high, the races may be further delayed or converted into a duathlon. Ensuring the Seine's cleanliness was always uncertain due to water quality variability.

title: 'Ahem Google!': Harris headlines in Trump searches? What Musk said
description: Elon Musk criticized Google for showing Kamala Harris in search results when users searched for Donald Trump. He suggested Google might be censoring Trump-related news ahead of the US elections. Musk also shared user posts claiming Google's positive bias towards censorship. In response, Google stated no manual actions were taken to alter search results.

title: Stock market today: BSE Sensex, Nifty50 lacklustre in opening trade
description: Stock market today: BSE Sensex and Nifty50, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened lacklustre in trade on Tuesday. While BSE Sensex was near 81,360, Nifty50 was above 24,800.

title: Viral video: When Raju & Srinath ran five runs off one ball vs Australia
description: Ireland's Lorcan Tucker and Andy McBrine completed an all-run five in their second innings during the one-off Test against Zimbabwe, sparking widespread excitement on social media. This event has gone viral, reminding cricket fans of a 1992 incident where India's No.10 and No.11 batters achieved an all-run five in a match against Australia.
